<br>
I have a high respect for those that show initiative (in any guild). So when I have no shows, I look for those present and willing. While I usually don't &quot;create&quot; new groups to account wait listers (Big raids are too crazy to manage), I will fill up any gaps until the group limits are met. I hate turning people down, but sometimes it just happens that way. I'm glad you could join us on this one.<br>
<br>
FYI, if you look at our calendar you'll notice last nights raid  entitled &quot;Lil HoT&quot;. As part of balancing HKD, I try and lead some raids for the lower crowd as well. This particular raid was 53+. We had quite a few people present, but had little knock down power. We also had many first timers. The raid would have struggled with anything more than a single or 2 non AoE. <br>
<br>
I encourage you guys to look out for an HKD/Amazon &quot;Very Hot&quot; raid (58+). Last time we did one in HKD we actually did a few 4 pulls!! Must admit though, it was an accident...but hey we lived!<br>
<br>
Also, every raid leader has his/her own style. I'm pretty much the miltary type (although I have no military background). I have a strict raid channel with very specific roles and procedures.For example,I never start raids late and replace or leave late comers (without prior notification). Absoluetly no chit chat in the channel (some folks make a chat channel for cutting up) While it sounds a bit harsh, raids are usually pretty smooth. Hope you adapted ok to this. <br>
<br>
See you guys soon!<br>
